block content
	section#thanks
		.page-header
			h1 Thank you
		p.lead Thank you for purchasing. If you have any questions that are beyond the scope of this documentation, please feel free to contact me. 
		P.lead By the way, if you like my plugin, please star it ★★★★★. Thank you so much! :)

	section#intro
		.page-header
			h1 Introduction
		p.lead "FlexMenu" is a fully responsive jQuery menu/navigation plugin. It was built with Sass CSS (Now also support Less) which makes it easy to modify.

	section#file-structure
		.page-header
			h1 File Structure
		p.lead Within the download you'll find the following file structure and contents
		p Once downloaded, unzip the compressed folder  and you'll see something like this:

		pre.prettyprint
			| flexmenu/
			| ├── Docs/
			| ├── Example - Basic/
			| ├── Example - Advanced/
			| └── Flexmenu/
		ul
			li
				strong "Docs"
				|  folder is where the help documentation is.
			li
				strong "Example - Baic"
				|  contains a simple example project.
			li
				strong "Example - Advanced"
				|  contains a much complex example project, which also includes Sass CSS and CoffeeScript files.
			li
				strong "Flexmenu"
				|  contains the minified version of flexmenu plugin.


	section#quick
		.page-header
			h1 Basic Usage
		p.lead You can refer to 
			strong Example - Basic
			|  file for code example. All you need to do is write some HTML, and one line jQuery code.
		p.lead Include the CSS and JS file
		p You need jQuery, since it's build on jQuery.
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- include the CSS and JS files --&gt;
			| &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="flexmenu/css/jquery.flexmenu.css"&gt;
			| &lt;script src="jquery-1.10.2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
			| &lt;script src="flexmenu/js/jquery.flexmenu.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

		P.lead The Menu:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- Menu container --&gt;
			| &lt;div class="fm-container"&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- Button --&gt;
			| 	&lt;div class="fm-button"&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fm-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fm-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fm-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 	&lt;/div&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- end button --&gt;

			| 	&lt;!-- Menu --&gt;
			| 	&lt;div class="menu"&gt;
			| 		&lt;ul&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 1&lt;/a&gt;
			| 				&lt;ul&gt;
			| 					&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Sub Item 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 					&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Sub Item 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 				&lt;/ul&gt;
			| 			&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 		&lt;/ul&gt;		
			| 	&lt;/div&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- end Menu --&gt;

			| &lt;/div&gt;
			| &lt;!-- end Menu container --&gt;

		P.lead Init, with one line jQuery code:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- init flexmenu --&gt;
			| &lt;script&gt;
			| $('.menu').flexMenu();
			| &lt;/script&gt;

		p.lead Again. You can refer to 
			strong Example - Basic
			|  file for code example. 

	section#usage
		.page-header
			h1 More options Usage
		p.lead There are some options avaiable.
		li breakpoint: 767
			| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
			| # Integer: The responsive breakpoint(px) of flexMenu
		li responsivePattern: 'toggle'
			| &nbsp;
			| # String: 'toggle' and 'off-canvas'
		li animationSpeed: 250
			| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
			| # Integer: The speed of animations, in milliseconds.
		br
		p So you can write you code this way:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			&lt;script&gt;
			| $('.menu').flexMenu({
			| 	breakpoint: 800,
			|	responsivePattern: 'off-canvas',
			|	animationSpeed: 300
			| });
			&lt;/script&gt;		
		p.lead Examples
		p You can also refer to the Examples - Advanced to see how things work.




